Center: OECD/NEA Nuclear Data Bank, Boulogne-Billancourt, France
title: -Double-Differential Neutron-Emission Cross Sections for Li-7 and Incident Neutrons Between 1.6 and 13.8 Me

x4codes.hlp: SCK CEN (Belgian Nuclear Research Centre), Mol, Belgium

x4freetext: FOR LI-7 AND INCIDENT NEUTRONS BETWEEN 1.6 AND 13.8 ME
150 MEV LINEAR ELECTRON ACCELERATOR OF THE CBNM
IN A MERCURY-COOLED ROTARY URANIUM TARGET
.7 CM DIAMETER METALLIC DISCS WITH AN ISOTOPIC
ENRICHMENT OF 99.97 PER CENT.TWO DIFFERENT SAMPLE
THICKNESSES WER USED.ONE VERY THIN (0.0324 AT/B) AND
.DATA CORRECTED BY AN OVERALL NORMALISATION UNCERTAINTY
+-50PER CENT OF THE CORRECTION RESULTING IN A
+-10PER CENT UNCERTAINTY IN THE TOTAL CROSS
SECTION RESULTING IN A (1-3)PER CENT UNCERTAINTY
+-30PER CENT OF THE CORRECTION RESULTING IN A
